    <briefdescription>
<para>Abstract base for all hardware-polled input objects. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Declare concrete input objects at global scope; the constructor self-registers into a static linked list. <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1a54bf0702b5027fc15906ca378515ad0b" kindref="member">PanelGroup::setup()</ref> calls <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1InputBase_1abffbb409d2f7a53cb075550e5bd35c0c" kindref="member">configure()</ref> on every registered input after chip initialisation, then calls <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1InputBase_1a9e8a36653bdad44ba8fcf005a2f1cf92" kindref="member">forceReport()</ref> for the boot EVT burst. <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1ab31c183f1fe58194e9c6e512fd9a0371" kindref="member">PanelGroup::loop()</ref> calls <ref refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1InputBase_1abe4599c9fd224766d742761261391b45" kindref="member">poll()</ref> every iteration. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
